.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fIDSA_do_sign()\fR computes a digital signature on the \fBlen\fR byte message
digest \fBdgst\fR using the private key \fBdsa\fR and returns it in a
newly allocated \fBDSA_SIG\fR structure.
.PP
the \fIDSA_sign_setup(3)|DSA_sign_setup(3)\fR manpage may be used to precompute part
of the signing operation in case signature generation is
time-critical.
.PP
\fIDSA_do_verify()\fR verifies that the signature \fBsig\fR matches a given
message digest \fBdgst\fR of size \fBlen\fR.  \fBdsa\fR is the signer's public
key.
.SH "RETURN VALUES"
\fIDSA_do_sign()\fR returns the signature, NULL on error.  \fIDSA_do_verify()\fR
returns 1 for a valid signature, 0 for an incorrect signature and \-1
on error. The error codes can be obtained by
the \fIERR_get_error(3)|ERR_get_error(3)\fR manpage.
